{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ee4400de-f44b-42ff-84d6-c1a607b04f8e","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results (not failed), and the reason string appears in the test output for traceability.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dbbc4a7e-2c09-451b-95a7-eb783f61b4bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":205,"requestId":"E3E0:1AA0D2:565AA9:6375B4:6A052397"},"id":"10e1d93f-07c2-4012-9673-0df2522a5db4","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:21:32.825Z","parentId":"d98d1238-48f2-4c42-8b74-ca60f6a5c6ae"}
